//! DSA signature provider â€” Rust port of
//! `providers/implementations/signature/dsa_sig.c`.
//!
//! This module implements the Digital Signature Algorithm (DSA) â€” FIPS 186-4 â€”
//! as a signature provider for the `openssl-provider` crate. It exposes one
//! composable algorithm entry (`"DSA"`) plus nine fixed `DSA-WITH-DIGEST`
//! sigalg combinations that mirror the nine `IMPL_DSA_SIGALG` dispatch tables
//! generated by the C source.
//!
//! # Supported algorithms
//!
//! | Algorithm name      | Digest      | OID                         | Variant |
//! |---------------------|-------------|-----------------------------|---------|
//! | `DSA`               | (any)       | 1.2.840.10040.4.1 (id-dsa)  | Composable |
//! | `DSA-SHA1`          | SHA1        | 1.2.840.10040.4.3           | Sigalg |
//! | `DSA-SHA224`        | SHA2-224    | 2.16.840.1.101.3.4.3.1      | Sigalg |
//! | `DSA-SHA256`        | SHA2-256    | 2.16.840.1.101.3.4.3.2      | Sigalg |
//! | `DSA-SHA384`        | SHA2-384    | 2.16.840.1.101.3.4.3.3      | Sigalg |
//! | `DSA-SHA512`        | SHA2-512    | 2.16.840.1.101.3.4.3.4      | Sigalg |
//! | `DSA-SHA3-224`      | SHA3-224    | 2.16.840.1.101.3.4.3.5      | Sigalg |
//! | `DSA-SHA3-256`      | SHA3-256    | 2.16.840.1.101.3.4.3.6      | Sigalg |
//! | `DSA-SHA3-384`      | SHA3-384    | 2.16.840.1.101.3.4.3.7      | Sigalg |
//! | `DSA-SHA3-512`      | SHA3-512    | 2.16.840.1.101.3.4.3.8      | Sigalg |
//!
//! # Key encoding (provider boundary)
//!
//! The provider boundary defined by [`SignatureContext::sign_init`] and
//! [`SignatureContext::verify_init`] passes key material as a length-prefixed
//! byte blob. Unlike EdDSA (fixed-size keys) or ECDSA (EC-point octet string),
//! DSA has three variable-size domain parameter components (`p`, `q`, `g`)
//! plus a private scalar (`x`) or public value (`y`). To carry all of these
//! through the `&[u8]` interface, the provider consumes a simple TLV blob:
//!
//! ```text
//! Byte 0:       version        = 0x01
//! Byte 1:       flags          (bit 0 = has_params, bit 1 = has_public, bit 2 = has_private)
//! If has_params (always required):
//!   u32 BE len_p, len_p bytes of big-endian p
//!   u32 BE len_q, len_q bytes of big-endian q
//!   u32 BE len_g, len_g bytes of big-endian g
//! If has_public (required for verify):
//!   u32 BE len_y, len_y bytes of big-endian y
//! If has_private (required for sign):
//!   u32 BE len_x, len_x bytes of big-endian x
//! ```
//!
//! Keys built by [`DsaKeyPair::from_components`](openssl_crypto::dsa::DsaKeyPair)
//! on the crypto layer are wrapped via this encoding by higher-layer key
//! management (see `providers/implementations/keymgmt/dsa.rs`). All parsing
//! occurs in safe Rust and every cryptographic operation is delegated to
//! [`openssl_crypto::dsa`] per Rule R8 (zero `unsafe` outside the FFI crate).
//!
//! # Signature format
//!
//! The [`openssl_crypto::dsa::sign`]/[`verify`](openssl_crypto::dsa::verify)
//! primitives return/accept a fixed-size `r || s` concatenation where each
//! half is `ceil(q_bits / 8)` bytes. This layer does not re-encode the
//! signature as DER. If DER serialization is required by a downstream
//! consumer (for example X.509), it is the responsibility of the CMS/X.509
//! layers to wrap the raw `r || s` into `ECDSA-Sig-Value` per RFC 3279.
//! This mirrors the decision made in `openssl_crypto::dsa`.
//!
//! # Deterministic nonces
//!
//! The C source supports FIPS 186-5 / RFC 6979 deterministic-`k` signing via
//! the `"nonce-type"` parameter. The current Rust crypto layer only supports
//! randomised nonces; requesting deterministic signing via [`NonceType`]
//! triggers a [`ProviderError::AlgorithmUnavailable`] error at context
//! initialisation.
//!
//! # C â†’ Rust mapping
//!
//! | C symbol (`dsa_sig.c`)                    | Rust symbol                                                                |
//! |-------------------------------------------|----------------------------------------------------------------------------|
//! | `PROV_DSA_CTX`                            | [`DsaSignatureContext`]                                                    |
//! | `OSSL_FUNC_signature_newctx_fn`           | [`DsaSignatureProvider::new_ctx`]                                          |
//! | `OSSL_FUNC_signature_freectx_fn`          | `Drop for DsaSignatureContext` (zeroizes automatically)                    |
//! | `OSSL_FUNC_signature_dupctx_fn`           | [`DsaSignatureContext::duplicate`]                                         |
//! | `OSSL_FUNC_signature_sign_init_fn`        | [`DsaSignatureContext::sign_init`]                                         |
//! | `OSSL_FUNC_signature_sign_fn`             | [`DsaSignatureContext::sign`]                                              |
//! | `OSSL_FUNC_signature_verify_init_fn`      | [`DsaSignatureContext::verify_init`]                                       |
//! | `OSSL_FUNC_signature_verify_fn`           | [`DsaSignatureContext::verify`]                                            |
//! | `OSSL_FUNC_signature_digest_sign_init_fn` | [`DsaSignatureContext::digest_sign_init`]                                  |
//! | `OSSL_FUNC_signature_digest_sign_update_fn` | [`DsaSignatureContext::digest_sign_update`]                              |
//! | `OSSL_FUNC_signature_digest_sign_final_fn`  | [`DsaSignatureContext::digest_sign_final`]                               |
//! | `OSSL_FUNC_signature_digest_verify_init_fn` | [`DsaSignatureContext::digest_verify_init`]                              |
//! | `OSSL_FUNC_signature_digest_verify_update_fn` | [`DsaSignatureContext::digest_verify_update`]                          |
//! | `OSSL_FUNC_signature_digest_verify_final_fn`  | [`DsaSignatureContext::digest_verify_final`]                           |
//! | `ossl_dsa_signature_functions`            | `dsa_signature_descriptor()`                                               |
//! | `ossl_dsa_sha1_signature_functions`       | `dsa_sha1_signature_descriptor()` (one per digest)                         |
//!
//! # Implementation rules honoured
//!
//! * **R5** â€” All nullable fields use `Option<T>`; [`NonceType`] enumerates
//!   legal values instead of `0`/`1` sentinels.
//! * **R6** â€” Numeric length conversions use `try_from`/`checked_*`.
//! * **R7** â€” No shared mutable state; each context is per-operation.
//! * **R8** â€” Zero `unsafe` blocks; all crypto is delegated.
//! * **R9** â€” Warning-free (`-D warnings`); all public items carry `///` docs.
//! * **R10** â€” Reachable via
//!   `openssl_provider::implementations::signatures::dsa::descriptors()`
//!   which is aggregated by `signatures::descriptors()` and ultimately
//!   wired into the default provider dispatch surface.

